            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_139gc' title='Col. 139GC &mdash; HL Deb 25 February 2004 vol 658 c139GC' name='column_139gc' href='#column_139gc' rel='bookmark'>139GC</a>
            General to conduct a compliance inspection on best value, a consultation with the Auditor General in advance of giving such a direction and the issue of guidance on best value. The amendments are not necessary as Section 29 of the <a href="/acts/local-government-act-1999">Local Government Act 1999</a> already substitutes the National Assembly for the Secretary of State in respect of Part 1 best-value provisions. Therefore, the responsibility lies with the National Assembly and not with the Secretary of State.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
